        <h2 class="mt-2">Critiquing Aesthetics in the 21st Century: Media's Adverse Impact on Public Perception of Beauty</h2>
        <p style="font-size:15px;"><i style="font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;"> Author : Payam Ghaznavi</i></p>
        <p>
            In the modern world of the 21st century, the concept of beauty has become one of the most debated issues in society. With technological advancements and the proliferation of social and digital media, people have grown accustomed to viewing beautiful images and content in every aspect of their daily lives. This shift in culture and human experience has sparked criticisms in the field of aesthetics.<br />

            Given the significance of beauty in human life, the study and critique of aesthetics in the 21st century are of paramount importance. On one hand, the media and digital platforms provide an excellent opportunity for sharing and disseminating beauty to a global audience. On the other hand, these media outlets can have profoundly negative effects on people's perception of beauty.
        </p>
