        <p>
            One of the primary negative influences of the media is the creation of unrealistic beauty standards. Often, the media presents images and models of beauty that cannot be compared to natural and real standards.This can lead to increased stress and anxiety among individuals regarding their personal appearance and beauty.<br />

            Furthermore, excessive media consumption and a focus on external beauty can diminish people's connection with inner beauty and the experience of beauty in nature and visual arts. This can reduce people's understanding of beauty as a personal and profound experience.<br />

            Ultimately, aesthetic critique in the 21st century should address both the positive and negative effects of media on our understanding of beauty and provide solutions to enhance our perception of beauty. Therefore, contemplating beauty as a multidimensional issue that encompasses not only physical appearance but also experiential and emotional aspects is crucial.<br />

            In conclusion, aesthetic critique in the 21st century can contribute to a better understanding of beauty and its effects on our lives. Striking a balance between external and internal beauty, as well as experiencing beauty as a personal and human process, can help us become the best versions of ourselves and experience the world around us more profoundly.<br />

            Considering the powerful impact of media on beauty and its perception, this critique of aesthetics emerges as a critical subject for evaluating and analyzing human life more comprehensively.






        </p>
